{"task_id": "task_101_11_obsidian_vault_audit", "category": "101_skill_usage", "task_yaml": {"task_id": "task_101_11_obsidian_vault_audit", "category": "101_skill_usage", "agent_sys": "openclaw", "agent_id": "main", "model": "gpt-5.4", "timeout_seconds": 1200, "max_total_seconds": 1800, "success_threshold": 0.9, "recording": "none", "headed": "auto", "task": "I'm about to lean heavily on my Obsidian vault for project planning next\nquarter, but I don't trust the state it's in — links rot, tags drift, and\nnotes go orphan without anyone noticing. Could you do a full health sweep\nof the vault at /tmp_workspace/clawbench/sources/vault/ using the Obsidian\nvault analysis skill so I can clean house before it matters?\n\nSave /tmp_workspace/results/report.md with three short sections covering\nthe note graph health, broken or stale references, and taxonomy cleanup\nwork you'd want me to do.\n\nIn the note-graph section list every orphan note you find — meaning a\nnote that nothing else in the vault links to. In the references section\nlist every wikilink whose target does not resolve, after you have applied\nObsidian's normal lookup rules so case-only or relative-path variants are\nnot treated as broken. In the taxonomy section group each cluster of\ncase- or hyphen-drifted tag variants together, including the file paths\nwhere each variant appears.\n\nEach bullet should give the affected file by vault-relative path and\nenough evidence for me to act on it.\n\nAlso save two handoff files:\n- /tmp_workspace/results/fix_plan.csv with columns issue_type,\n  affected_path, evidence, proposed_fix, priority. Include every issue\n  you found that needs a content or linking fix — every orphan, every\n  broken wikilink, and every tag-drift cluster.\n- /tmp_workspace/results/tag_normalization.json mapping each drifted tag\n  variant to the normalized tag you recommend, with one object per\n  cluster and a short reason. Pick the form most files seem to be\n  migrating toward, not a mechanical default. Also include the total\n  use-count for each variant so I can sanity-check the majority signal.\n", "sources": ["vault/"], "skills": ["obsidian"], "services": [{"name": "task-setup", "path": "task-setup", "start": "bash install.sh", "oneshot": true}], "codex": {"max_user_followups": 2}}, "prompt": "I'm about to lean heavily on my Obsidian vault for project planning next\nquarter, but I don't trust the state it's in — links rot, tags drift, and\nnotes go orphan without anyone noticing. Could you do a full health sweep\nof the vault at /tmp_workspace/clawbench/sources/vault/ using the Obsidian\nvault analysis skill so I can clean house before it matters?\n\nSave /tmp_workspace/results/report.md with three short sections covering\nthe note graph health, broken or stale references, and taxonomy cleanup\nwork you'd want me to do.\n\nIn the note-graph section list every orphan note you find — meaning a\nnote that nothing else in the vault links to. In the references section\nlist every wikilink whose target does not resolve, after you have applied\nObsidian's normal lookup rules so case-only or relative-path variants are\nnot treated as broken. In the taxonomy section group each cluster of\ncase- or hyphen-drifted tag variants together, including the file paths\nwhere each variant appears.\n\nEach bullet should give the affected file by vault-relative path and\nenough evidence for me to act on it.\n\nAlso save two handoff files:\n- /tmp_workspace/results/fix_plan.csv with columns issue_type,\n  affected_path, evidence, proposed_fix, priority. Include every issue\n  you found that needs a content or linking fix — every orphan, every\n  broken wikilink, and every tag-drift cluster.\n- /tmp_workspace/results/tag_normalization.json mapping each drifted tag\n  variant to the normalized tag you recommend, with one object per\n  cluster and a short reason. Pick the form most files seem to be\n  migrating toward, not a mechanical default. Also include the total\n  use-count for each variant so I can sanity-check the majority signal.\n", "eval_rule_md": "", "assets": {"privacy": null, "skills": ["obsidian"], "sources": [{"name": "vault", "path": "vault", "is_dir": true, "children": [{"name": "Archive", "path": "vault/Archive", "is_dir": true, "children": [{"name": "deprecated-process.md", "path": "vault/Archive/deprecated-process.md", "is_dir": false, "size": 149, "url": "http://100.116.9.115:9018/injection/101_skill_usage/task_101_11_obsidian_vault_audit/sources/vault/Archive/deprecated-process.md"}, {"name": "old-vendor-notes.md", "path": "vault/Archive/old-vendor-notes.md", "is_dir": false, "size": 142, "url": "http://100.116.9.115:9018/injection/101_skill_usage/task_101_11_obsidian_vault_audit/sources/vault/Archive/old-vendor-notes.md"}, {"name": "old_idea_2019.md", "path": "vault/Archive/old_idea_2019.md", "is_dir": false, "size": 74, "url": "http://100.116.9.115:9018/injection/101_skill_usage/task_101_11_obsidian_vault_audit/sources/vault/Archive/old_idea_2019.md"}]}, {"name": "areas", "path": "vault/areas", "is_dir": true, "children": [{"name": "customer-onboarding.md", "path": "vault/areas/customer-onboarding.md", "is_dir": false, "size": 172, "url": "http://100.116.9.115:9018/injection/101_skill_usage/task_101_11_obsidian_vault_audit/sources/vault/areas/customer-onboarding.md"}, {"name": "reliability.md", "path": "vault/areas/reliability.md", "is_dir": false, "size": 166, "url": "http://100.116.9.115:9018/injection/101_skill_usage/task_101_11_obsidian_vault_audit/sources/vault/areas/reliability.md"}, {"name": "security.md", "path": "vault/areas/security.md", "is_dir": false, "size": 222, "url": "http://100.116.9.115:9018/injection/101_skill_usage/task_101_11_obsidian_vault_audit/sources/vault/areas/security.md"}]}, {"name": "checklists", "path": "vault/checklists", "is_dir": true, "children": [{"name": "alpha-rollout.md", "path": "vault/checklists/alpha-rollout.md", "is_dir": false, "size": 179, "url": "http://1